---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Methodology — 2112 Capital Solutions"
  description="Documented engagement sequence. Five steps from intake to retainer. Each step has explicit inputs, outputs, and a clean termination point if we're not a fit."
>
  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="classify">MODULE 02 — METHODOLOGY · SEQ.001 → SEQ.005</div>
      <h1>How an engagement <em>runs.</em></h1>
      <div class="hero-sub">
        Documented sequence · Explicit inputs and outputs · Clean termination point at any stage · No expiring quotes, no pressure tactics
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- METHOD STEPS -->
  <section class="module">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="module-classify">
        <span>SEQUENCE</span>
        <span class="ref">SEQ.001 → SEQ.005</span>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="method-step-num"><b>SEQ.001</b>INTAKE</div>
        <div>
          <h5>Free 30-minute call</h5>
          <p>Direct conversation about where you are, what you have, and what success looks like. No pitch. We tell you what we'd do; you decide whether we should. If you've already decided this isn't your firm, the call costs nothing and you walk away with our perspective.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="method-step-num"><b>SEQ.002</b>SCOPING</div>
        <div>
          <h5>Written engagement memo</h5>
          <p>Deliverables, timeline, price, risks, and termination conditions documented. You sign or you don't. No expiring quotes, no pressure tactics. The memo is yours to keep regardless.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="method-step-num"><b>SEQ.003</b>EXECUTION</div>
        <div>
          <h5>One operator on file</h5>
          <p>Same operator from start to finish. We don't subcontract custody work. The person you talked to in intake is the person doing the work. You have their direct contact for the duration of the engagement.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="method-step-num"><b>SEQ.004</b>HANDOVER</div>
        <div>
          <h5>Documented runbook</h5>
          <p>Every engagement closes with a written runbook covering recovery, rotation, and ongoing maintenance procedures. The runbook is yours to keep, signed and dated. We rehearse the procedures with you in your presence before sign-off.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="method-step">
        <div class="method-step-num"><b>SEQ.005</b>RETAINER</div>
        <div>
          <h5>Ongoing stewardship · optional</h5>
          <p>For node infrastructure and treasury work, a monthly retainer covers patching, rotation, and quarterly health checks. Cancellable on 30 days notice. No long-term contracts.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PRINCIPLES -->
  <section class="module">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="module-classify">
        <span>OPERATING PRINCIPLES</span>
        <span class="ref">WHAT WE REFUSE · WHAT WE COMMIT</span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="module-title">What we <em>refuse.</em></h2>
      <p class="module-lede">No paywalls. No email walls. No tracking analytics. No interstitials. No urgency or scarcity language. No discovery-call-only pricing. No founder-cult of personality. The combination of refusal and commitment is the stewardship statement.</p>

      <div class="references">
        <h6>— What we commit to</h6>
        <ol>
          <li>Real prices for real services. Self-custody $100+, node setup $500+, advisory $100/hr.</li>
          <li>Named testimonials with full attribution. No anonymous quotes.</li>
          <li>Source-linked guides. Every claim traceable.</li>
          <li>Long-form transparency on what each service includes.</li>
          <li>Booking calendar visible without form-gating.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
